{{Infobox film | name =93 Days | image =93 Days.jpeg | alt = | caption = | film name = | director =Steve Gukas | producer ={{plainlist| *[[Bolanle Austen-Peters]] *Dotun Olakunri *Pemon Rami}} | writer = Paul Rowlston | screenplay = | story = | based on = [[Ebola virus disease in Nigeria]] | starring ={{Plainlist| *[[Bimbo Akintola]] *[[Danny Glover]] *[[Somkele Iyamah|Somkele Idhalama]] *[[Bimbo Manuel]] *Sola Oyebade}} | narrator = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | production companies ={{plainlist| *Native FilmWorks *Michel Angelo Production *Bolanle Austen-Peters Production}} | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2016|09|16|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web | url=https://tns.ng/nollywood-films-set-break-box-office-records-2016/ | title=TNS EXCLUSIVE: Nollywood Films Set To Break Box Office Records In 2016 | publisher=TNS | date=18 July 2016 | accessdate=12 August 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817202746/https://tns.ng/nollywood-films-set-break-box-office-records-2016/ | archive-date=2016-08-17 | dead-url=yes | df= }}</ref> | runtime = | country =Nigeria | language =English }}
'''''93 Days''''' is a 2016 Nigerian [[drama]] [[thriller film]] directed and co-produced by [[Steve Gukas]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/danny-glover-tim-reid-at-unveiling-of-ebola-movie-93-days-/219950/ | title=Danny Glover, Tim Reid at Unveiling of Ebola Movie ‘93 Days’ | work=[[Thisday|ThisDay Newspaper]] | date=11 September 2015 | accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> It tells the story of the [[Ebola virus disease in Nigeria|2014 Ebola outbreak in Nigeria]] and its successful containment by health workers from a [[Lagos]] hospital. It stars [[Bimbo Akintola]], [[Danny Glover]] and [[Bimbo Manuel]] with joint-production through Native FilmWorks, Michel Angelo Production and Bolanle Austen-Peters Production.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/coming-soon-93-days-a-film-on-ebola/218219/ | title=Coming Soon…93 Days, A Film on Ebola | work=[[Thisday|ThisDay Newspaper]] | date=23 August 2015 | accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>
==Background== The story of ''93 Days'' centres on the sacrifices made by men and women who risked their lives to make sure the [[Ebola virus]] was contained, before it becomes an epidemic, when it was imported into Nigeria by a Liberian American diplomat.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://thenationonlineng.net/93-days-filmmakers-narrate-complexity-of-ebola-in-new-movie/ | title=93 Days: Filmmakers narrate complexity of Ebola in new movie | work=[[The Nation (Nigeria)|The Nation]] | date=26 August 2015 | accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> ''93 Days'' is also dedicated to [[Ameyo Adadevoh]], a Nigerian physician who played a key role in the containment of Ebola in Nigeria. The movie was directed by Steve Gukas and was shot in several parts of Nigeria.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.naij.com/535848-ebola-scare-popular-nollywood-actress-turns-doctor-photos.html | title=Actress Bimbo Akintola Turned Doctor In 93 Days | work=[[Naij]] | date=31 August 2015 | accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>
