{{infobox book | | name = How to Be a Jewish Mother, a very lovely training manual | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:HowToBeAJewishMother.jpg | caption = First edition | author = [[Dan Greenburg]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | genre = | publisher = [[Price Stern Sloan]] | pub_date = October 1964<ref name="suss1"/> | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 99 | isbn = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''How to Be a Jewish Mother''''' is a 1964 [[Jewish humor]] book by American [[humorist]] [[Dan Greenburg]] which was the best selling non-fiction book in the United States in 1965, with 270,000 copies sold.<ref name="ref1">Hackett, Alice Payne. [https://books.google.com/books?id=cOI8AQAAIAAJ Seventy years of best sellers, 1895-1965], p. 227 (1967)</ref><ref name="books">[https://books.google.com/books?ei=-WM-UJDbGsm16AHJ7oGIDw&id=s-5OAAAAIAAJ&dq= The Bookseller] ("Non-Fiction. The bestseller of the year in non- fiction was a book called How to Be a Jewish Mother, by Dan Greenburg")</ref><ref name="maaaa">Bernstein, Fred A. [https://books.google.com/books?id=zPl2wNG0EDwC&pg=PT23#v=onepage&q&f=false The Jewish Mothers' Hall of Fame] (chapter on Leah Greenburg and the book) (1986)</ref> The book was first published by [[Price Stern Sloan]] under publisher [[Larry Sloan]].<ref name=pw>{{cite news|first=Wendy|last=Werris|title=Obituary: Larry Sloan, 89 |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/authors/obituaries/article/54394-obituary-larry-sloan-89.html |work=[[Publishers Weekly]] |publisher= |date=2012-10-15 |accessdate=2012-11-17}}</ref><ref name=time>{{cite news|first=Regina|last=Wang|title=‘Mad Libs’ Publisher Larry Sloan Dies |url=http://newsfeed.time.com/2012/10/18/mad-libs-publisher-larry-sloan-dies/ |work=[[Time Magazine]] |publisher= |date=2012-10-18 |accessdate=2012-11-17}}</ref>
The book was adapted into a play starring [[Molly Picon]] and [[Godfrey Cambridge]] which had a brief run on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] at the [[Hudson Theater]] from December 1967 through January 1968.<ref name="suss1">Battaglio, Stephen. [https://books.google.com/books?id=E1TT4POdbGUC&pg=PA251&lpg=PA251&dq=%22how+to+be+a+jewish+mother%22+greenburg+1964&source=bl&ots=Bg6JubtWVT&sig=aOio-ebd2GYmYVzxv4PMwDoTr-E&hl=en&sa=X&ei=i2Y-UK6FLOyI6AHs7YD4Bg&ved=0CEAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22how%20to%20be%20a%20jewish%20mother%22%20greenburg%201964&f=false David Susskind: A Televised Life], p. 251 (2010)</ref><ref name="play1">(29 December 1967). [https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FA0917F93B5B127A93CBAB1789D95F438685F9 Theater: 'How to Be a Jewish Mother'; Molly Picon Stars With Godfrey Cambridge], ''[[The New York Times]]''</ref>
The play was profiled in the [[William Goldman]] book ''[[The Season: A Candid Look at Broadway]]''.
A 1983 French adaptation, ''Comment devenir une mère juive en 10 leçons'', met with long-running success.<ref name="france1">(10 March 2001). [http://www.leparisien.fr/loisirs-et-spectacles/une-mere-juive-joyeuse-et-drole-10-03-2001-2002017421.php Une mère juive joyeuse et drôle], ''[[Le Parisien]]'' (in French)</ref><ref name="french2">(6 October 2004). [http://www.lemagazine.info/?Comment-devenir-une-mere-juive Comment devenir une mère juive....], ''lemagazine.info'' (in French)</ref> [[Gertrude Berg]] also released a best-selling comedy album from the book in 1965.<ref name="suss1"/>
It was re-issued as a mass market paperback in 1991 ({{ISBN|0843100206}}, {{ISBN|9780843100204}}).
