{{Infobox artist | name = Varlen Pen | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = September 29, 1916 | birth_place = [[Russian Empire]] | death_date = May 26, 1990 | death_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] | field = [[Painting]] | citizenship = [[USSR]] | nationality = | training = [[Repin Institute of Arts]] | movement = [[Realism (visual art)|Realism]] | works = | patrons = | awards = }}
'''Pen Varlen''' ({{lang-ru|Пен Варлен}}; {{lang-ko|변월룡}}; September 29, 1916, [[Russian Empire]]; May 26, 1990, [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]]) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Russians|Russian]] — [[Koreans|Korean]] painter and graphic artist, a member of the [[Saint Petersburg Union of Artists|Leningrad Union of Artists]],<ref>''Справочник членов Ленинградской организации Союза художников РСФСР.'' Л., Художник РСФСР, 1987. C.89.</ref> lived and worked in [[Leningrad]], regarded as a representative of the [[Leningrad School of Painting|Leningrad school of painting]],<ref>''Sergei V. Ivanov. Unknown Socialist Realism. The Leningrad School.'' Saint Petersburg, NP-Print Edition, 2007. P.366, 387, 391, 395.</ref> most famous for his portrait paintings.
